13/04/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- President George W. 
Bush on Friday (11 April) formally asked the Senate to approve the latest enlargement of NATO. 
"The president is very pleased that the Senate will now be able to vote on expanding NATO to Bulgaria, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, Romania, Slovakia and Slovenia," said White House spokesman Ari Fleischer. 
The parliaments of the member-states are expected to ratify the enlargement within the next 12 months.
In other news, the House of Representatives held a rare Saturday session to pass Bush's war budget, following Senate approval late Friday. 
The package includes $7.9 billion in foreign aid. 
Turkey will get $1 billion. 
(AP, AFP, Reuters, CNN, BBC - 12/04/2003)
